However, Wikipedia data shows that for nominal GDP per capita in 2023-2024, several countries/territories rank higher than Singapore: Monaco ($256,581), Liechtenstein ($207,973), Luxembourg ($140,941), and Bermuda ($138,935)

The CIA World Factbook uses purchasing power parity (PPP) adjustments which accounts for cost of living differences, while Wikipedia uses nominal GDP per capita which doesn't adjust for cost differences
Different measurement methodologies (PPP vs nominal) produce different rankings, making the claim ambiguous as it doesn't specify which metric is being used
Singapore consistently ranks in the top 5 globally for GDP per capita across different sources, but whether it is definitively #1 depends on the specific measurement method used
